///////////////////////
// Compilation
///////////////////////

We used:
	1.- CMake v3.14.0

We heavily recommend you to follow the official guides to compile each dependencie.
	Ogre3D: https://ogrecave.github.io/ogre/api/1.11/building-ogre.html
	CEGUI: http://static.cegui.org.uk/docs/0.8.7/build_options.html
	OIS: https://github.com/wgois/OIS
	Bullet3: https://github.com/wolfviking0/webcl-bullet3

CMake:
	1.- Open the dependencie folder with the source code
	2.- Setup a folder inside of it called "Build" to build the binaries into.
	3.- Run Configure button to visualize all the possible options, once defined, run configure again.
	4.- Choose only those needed for the project and correlated to Ogre3D.
	5.- Run Generate for Visual Studio 2017 x64.

Now go ahead to the "Build folder" and run the new Visual Studio Project.
Run each project in Debug and Release Mode.
Now the builds are done, save the build directory.

